.TH asinh 3
.SH NAME
.PP
\*Lasinh\*O, \*Lacosh\*O, \*Latanh\*O \- Computes inverse hyperbolic functions
.SH LIBRARY
.PP
\*OMath Library (\*Llibm.a\*O)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <math.h>
.PP
\*Ldouble asinh  (\*Ldouble \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Lfloat  asinhf (\*Lfloat  \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Ldouble atanh  (\*Ldouble \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Lfloat  atanhf (\*Lfloat  \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Ldouble acosh  (\*Ldouble \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Lfloat  acoshf (\*Lfloat  \*Vx\*L);\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "arc tangent" "hyperbolic function"
.iX "arc sine" "hyperbolic function"
.iX "arc cosine" "hyperbolic function"
.iX "hyperbolic functions" "asinh"
.iX "hyperbolic functions" "acosh"
.iX "hyperbolic functions" "atanh"
.iX "asinh function"
.iX "acosh function"
.iX "atanh function"
The \*Lasinh(\|)\*O and \*Lasinhf(\|)\*O
functions return the hyperbolic arc sine of \*Vx\*O,
in the range [-infinity, +infinity] where
asinh(\*Vx\*O) = ln(\*Vx\*O + sqrt(\*Vx\*O**2 + 1)).
.PP
The \*Lacosh(\|)\*O  and \*Lacoshf(\|)\*O functions
return the hyperbolic arc cosine of \*Vx\*O, in the range [1, +infinity] where
acosh(\*Vx\*O) = ln (\*Vx\*O + sqrt(\*Vx\*O**2 - 1)).
.PP
The \*Latanh(\|)\*O and \*Latanhf(\|)\*O functions return the hyperbolic arc
tangent of \*Vx\*O, in the range (-1, 1). atanh() is the reverse
function of tanh() where atanh(tanh(\*Vx\*O)) = \*Vx\*O.
.\".iS
.\"EXCEPTIONAL CASES
.\"
.\"        Function       Exceptional Argument   Routine Behavior
.\"        ---------      --------------------   ---------------------
